@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "About the project";
}

<div id="gbmainbg">
    <div id="menu" class="menu">
        <img class="option" src="~/icons/home-w.png" title="back to home" onclick="javascript:location.href = '/'" />
        <img class="option" src="~/icons/info-w.png" title="info" onclick="javascript:location.href='/info'" />
    </div>

    <div id="loc" class="location">
        <a href="https://maps.app.goo.gl/hbQkUNNToMNu8HFx9" target="_blank"><img class="option"
                src="~/icons/location-w.png" title="image info" /></a>
    </div>

    <div id="location-info">
        Turkey, Kekova
    </div>

    <div id="info-secondbg">
        <div id="info-set">

            <div id="user-manual" class="info-text" style="display: none;">
                <div class="info-header-container">
                    <div class="info-header" id="manual-header"><b>User Manual</b></div>
                    <div class="info-divider">|</div>
                    <div class="info-header" id="about-header" onclick="showAboutProject()">About the Project</div>
                </div>
                <h1>Getting Started</h1>
                <p>The MCT Timer helps instructors run classroom breaks, labs, and resume reminders from a public timer page.</p>

                <h2>Start a timer</h2>
                <p>Choose a preset button on the right or enter a resume time, select AM/PM, and click <strong>START</strong>. Use the quick adjustment buttons to jump to the top of the next hour or add/remove minutes before starting.</p>

                <h2>Session details</h2>
                <p>Add a session title, customer, location, class hours, and instructor name. These appear as a compact banner across the top of the countdown page.</p>

                <h2>Instructor LinkedIn and QR code</h2>
                <p>Paste an instructor LinkedIn profile URL and, optionally, a public QR-code image URL. The bundled QR image is available at <code>/profile/linkedin-qr.png</code>. The countdown page shows the link and QR code at the bottom of the screen.</p>

                <h2>Spotify playlist music</h2>
                <p>Paste a Spotify playlist URL, Spotify URI, embed URL, or playlist ID. The countdown page shows a Spotify embed player. Spotify music does not autoplay; click the player or the playlist control to start it.</p>

                <h2>Showcase media and video</h2>
                <p>Add a public image, GIF, MP4/WebM/Ogg video, YouTube URL, or Vimeo URL to show references, upcoming topics, or promotional content beside the timer. Videos autoplay muted and loop when browser and provider policy allow it.</p>

                <h2>Backgrounds</h2>
                <p>The countdown page uses the latest Bing image by default. If AI background generation is selected and configured, the generated image replaces Bing. If AI fails, the timer falls back to Bing automatically.</p>
            </div>

            <div id="about-project" class="info-text">
                <div class="info-header-container">
                    <div class="info-header" id="manual-header" onclick="showUserManual()">User Manual</div>
                    <div class="info-divider">|</div>
                    <div class="info-header" id="about-header"> <b>About the Project</b></div>
                </div>
                <h1>Project Hosting</h1>
                <p>The MCT Timer is an open source classroom countdown timer for trainers, instructors, and event hosts.
                    It is designed to run as a lightweight ASP.NET Core web app and can be hosted in Azure or your own
                    preferred environment.</p>
                <p>The active project repository is <a href="https://github.com/dngoins/mct-timer"
                        target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://github.com/dngoins/mct-timer</a>. Use the
                    repository to review the source code, deploy your own copy, report issues, or suggest improvements.</p>
                <p>One of the core principles of the MCT Timer project is accessibility. The timer is public, easy to
                    share, and does not require learners to sign in, making it useful for classrooms, workshops, online
                    events, and breaks.</p>
                <h1>Features and Benefits</h1>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Easy setup:</strong> The web interface is user-friendly, allowing trainers to quickly set up timers with
                        minimal effort.</li>
                    <li><strong>Real-time resume notifications:</strong> Learners are promptly informed when classes will resume, ensuring that
                        everyone stays on schedule.</li>
                    <li><strong>Public access:</strong> The site is accessible to all, fostering a collaborative and inclusive learning
                        environment.</li>
                    <li><strong>Flexible timer presets:</strong> Quick buttons and manual time entry help instructors start common break,
                        lunch, lab, or wait timers quickly.</li>
                    <li><strong>Session branding:</strong> Add the class title, customer, location, hours, and instructor so the timer doubles
                        as a useful classroom information screen.</li>
                    <li><strong>Spotify playlist support:</strong> Add optional playlist music with Spotify public embeds while keeping
                        playback under user control.</li>
                    <li><strong>Showcase media:</strong> Display images, GIFs, videos, YouTube, or Vimeo content beside the countdown for
                        announcements, agendas, or sponsor/reference material.</li>
                    <li><strong>Instructor profile sharing:</strong> Add a LinkedIn profile and QR code so learners can connect after class.</li>
                    <li><strong>Modern backgrounds:</strong> Use the Bing image of the day by default, generate AI backgrounds when configured,
                        or use custom backgrounds for different timer types.</li>
                    <li><strong>Lightweight deployment:</strong> The app does not require Spotify credentials or paid/private media APIs, and it
                        can be deployed into your own Azure subscription.</li>
                </ul>
                <h1>Feedback and Contact</h1>
                <p>Feedback and ideas are welcome. To report a bug, request a feature, or contribute a change, visit the
                    <a href="https://github.com/dngoins/mct-timer/issues" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Dngoins MCT Timer issues page</a>.</p>
                <h1>Conclusion</h1>
                <p>The MCT Timer supports smoother learning experiences by combining clear countdowns, session context,
                    music, media, and instructor information in one shareable classroom display.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

    </div>

</div>

@section Scripts
{
        <script>
            function menuUpdate() {
                outOfScrollPosition(document.querySelector("#gbmainbg"), document.querySelector("#menu"));
                outOfScrollPosition(document.querySelector("#gbmainbg"), document.querySelector("#loc"));
            }

            function showUserManual() {
                document.getElementById("user-manual").style.display = "block";
                document.getElementById("about-project").style.display = "none";
                document.getElementById("manual-header").classList.add("active");
                document.getElementById("about-header").classList.remove("active");
            }

            function showAboutProject() {
                document.getElementById("user-manual").style.display = "none";
                document.getElementById("about-project").style.display = "block";
                document.getElementById("about-header").classList.add("active");
                document.getElementById("manual-header").classList.remove("active");
            }

            $(document).ready(function () {
                document.querySelector("#gbmainbg").style.backgroundImage = "url(/bg-lib/info.jpg)";
                menuUpdate();
                showUserManual(); // Show User Manual by default
            })

            $(window).resize(() => menuUpdate());

        </script>
}
